This callback will called when the user click on the map and response a LatLng object
which contains all information about the location where user click

desc:

This callback will called when the navigation is cancelled
(user click on the cancel button on the navigation view)

name: onNavigationFinished
desc: This callback will called when the navigation is finished (user arrived destination)

name: onNavigationRunning
desc: This callback will called when the navigation is running

name: onNewRouteSelected

This callback will called when the user select a new route and response a DirectionRoute object

name: onRouteBuildFailed

name: onRouteBuilding

name: onRouteBuilt

This callback will called when the route is built successfully and response a DirectionRoute object
which contains all information about the route

name: onRouteProgressChange
desc:
This callback will called whenever user change GPS location
it will response a RouteProgressEvent object, which contains all information about current route

name: userOffRoute
desc:
This callback will called when the user is off route and response a LatLng object
which contains all information about the location where user off route
(user is off route when user is not follow the route)

desc: A constant List of the values in this enum, in order of their declaration.

name: MapOptions
desc: Configuration options for the MapBoxNavigation.

name: allowsUTurnAtWayPoints
desc:
If the value of this property is true, a returned route may require an
immediate U-turn at an intermediate waypoint. At an intermediate waypoint,
if the value of this property is false, each returned route may continue
straight ahead or turn to either side but may not U-turn. This property
has no effect if only two waypoints are specified.
same as 'not continueStraight' on Android

name: alternatives
desc: When true, alternate routes will be presented

name: animateBuildRoute
desc: Should animate the building of the Route. Default is True

name: apiKey
desc: Vietmap routing api key, contact vietmap.vn to get a key

name: bearing
desc:
Bearing is the direction that the camera is pointing in and
measured in degrees clockwise from north.

name: customLocationCenterIcon
desc: Location center custom icon, get by call VietMapHelper.getBytesFromAsset('assetsPath')

name: initialLatitude
desc: The initial Latitude of the Map View

name: initialLongitude
desc: The initial Longitude of the Map View

name: isOptimized
desc:
if true, will reorder the routes to optimize navigation for time and
shortest distance using the Travelling Salesman Algorithm.
Always false for now

name: language
desc:
2-letter ISO 639-1 code for language. This property affects the sentence
contained within the RouteStep.instructions property, but it does not
affect any road names contained in that property or other properties
such as RouteStep.name. Defaults to 'en' if an unsupported language
is specified. The languages in this link are supported:

name: longPressDestinationEnabled
desc:
When the user long presses on a point on the map, set that
as the destination

name: mapStyle
desc: Vietmap map style url, contact vietmap.vn to get a map style url

name: mapStyleUrlDay
desc: The Url of the style the Navigation MapView should use during the day

name: mapStyleUrlNight
desc: The Url of the style the Navigation MapView should use at night

name: mode
desc: The navigation mode desired. Defaults to drivingWithTraffic

name: padding
desc: Padding applied to the MapView when embedded

name: showEndOfRouteFeedback
desc: In iOS this will show/hide the end of route page when navigation is done. Default to True.

name: showReportFeedbackButton
desc: In iOS this will show/hide the feedback button. Default to True.

name: simulateRoute
desc:
if true will simulate the route as if you were driving.
Always true on iOS Simulator

name: tilt
desc:
Tilt is the camera's angle from the nadir (directly facing the Earth)
and uses unit degrees. The camera's minimum (default) tilt is 0 degrees,
and the maximum tilt is 60. Tilt levels use six decimal point of
precision, which enables you to restrict/set/lock a map's bearing
with extreme precision.

name: trackCameraPosition
desc:
If true, the map will continuously update the user location
when the location changes. Defaults to true.

name: units
desc: The unit of measure said in voice instructions

name: zoom
desc:
Zoom controls the scale of the map and consumes any value between 0
and 22. At zoom level 0, the viewport shows continents and other world
features. A middle value of 11 will show city level details, and at a
higher zoom level, the map will begin to show buildings and
points of interest.

name: RouteEvent
desc: Represents an event sent by the navigation service

name: RouteLeg
desc:
A RouteLeg object defines a single leg of a route between two waypoints.
If the overall route has only two waypoints, it has a single RouteLeg object that covers the entire route.
The route leg object includes information about the leg, such as its name, distance, and expected travel time.
Depending on the criteria used to calculate the route, the route leg object may also include detailed turn-by-turn instructions.

name: RouteProgressEvent
desc:
This class contains all progress information at any given time during a navigation session.
This progress includes information for the current route, leg and step the user is traversing along.
With every new valid location update, a new route progress will be generated using the latest information.

name: currentLeg
desc: Current leg the user is traversing along.

name: currentLocation
desc: Current location of the user, this is the raw location from the location provider

name: currentModifier
desc: currentModifierType and currentModifier is an additional instruction on how to complete the current step.

name: currentModifierType
desc:
Current modifier of the step the user is on.
currentModifierType and currentModifier is an additional instruction on how to complete the current step.

name: currentStepInstruction
desc: Text instruction for the current step the user is on.

name: distanceToNextTurn
desc: Distance to the next turn, in meters.

name: snappedLocation
desc:
Current snapped location of the user, this is the location snapped to the route
This value will stable if the user is not moving
The location is always on the route, if the user is off route, the location will be snapped to the nearest point on the route

name: RouteStep
desc:
A RouteStep object represents a single distinct maneuver along a route and the approach to the next maneuver.
The route step object corresponds to a single instruction the user must follow to complete a portion of the route.
For example, a step might require the user to turn then follow a road.

name: VoiceUnits

Whether or not the units used inside the voice instruction's string are
in imperial or metric.
